description: generic association between an entity and an ontological term
mixin for a denormalized class. A denormalized class is formed from a join of two or more other classes
root class for association or entity documents
mixin for any association that is GO related
mixin for a normalized class, in the sense of database normal forms

line of xAF. xAF is a generalization of GAF designed to work for other ontologies than GO, and for other entities beyond genes and proteins. xAF has the same column headers to GAF, but has fewer restrictions.
